It’s simple to make, you’ll need:
-1/2 cup almond butter
 -1/2 cup coconut oil
-1/2 cup of cacao butter
 -1/2 cup cacao powder @sunfood 
- 2 tbsp of monkfruit sugar @lakanto 

Directions:
In stove top combine almond butter and coconut oil in low heat until it thickens up. Then put in muffin liners, refrigerate for 20 min. While the almond butter is the fridge, heat up cacao butter, cacao & sugar in low heat until it thickens. The final step is put this on top of the almond butter. Refrigerate for another 20 minutes. 
Quick tip - this melts easily so it needs to stay in the fridge & take it out when you are ready to eat. 😍

Recipe 👇 Beef flautas 
**recipe is also on the blog (link in bio)
Ingredients:
✨Ground Beef
* 1 lb Ground Beef
* 1/2 tsp cumin
* 1/2 tsp oregano
* 1/2 tsp garlic powder
* 1 tbsp avocado oil cooking spray

✨Avocado Cream
* 2 tbsp fresh lime juice
* 1 avocado
* pinch of salt (to taste)
* 1/2 cup sour cream (or non dairy sour cream)
12 6″inch corn or flour tortilla
**use corn tortilla for gluten free option
Toppings
* Avocado Cream
* 1/2 diced fresh tomato
* 1/4 fresh dice onion 1/2 cup cilantro
Directions:
Ground Beef
* In a medium size pan, in high heat spray avocado oil spray. Once hot, add ground beef, cook until brown. Add cumin, oregano and garlic powder.
* Preheat oven to 425 degrees
* For each flauta, spoon about 2 tbsp beef mixture onto a tortilla
* Roll each tortilla up tightly and place seam-side down on baking pan/sheet
* Assemble all flautas one at time until you’re done.
* Once all assembled spray the tops with avocado oil spray
* Bake for 20 minutes until nice golden brown
Toppings
* Avocado cream
* Mash ripe avocado with a fork. Add in lime & sour cream, mix until combined. Season with salt. Add more lime & salt for tasting. Refrigerate until use.
* Serve flautas with avocado cream, cilantro, onions & tomato

80/20 lifestyle | balancing wellness and fun |

Eating mainly nutritious foods makes me feel good, but eating ‘fun foods’ are so important too. I’ve learned that too much restriction is stressful. 

Instead of trying and eating “perfectly” and then have a “cheat day,” now I incorporate all my favorite foods into my meals over the course of the week.. it’s more flexible and easier. 

As far as my workouts, I don’t do any programs. I sign up for classes on @classpass to make sure I go 🥰I love doing weights, barre, yoga and Pilates classes. Working out for me gives me the best energy to be productive throughout the day.

Ofcourse there are days I’m too tired, I listen to what my body needs….If I need to rest, then I chill & watch my favorite shows. 

Follow me for more easy recipes, drinks and favorite eats @dietandfries

Balancing life. Here’s a few tips:

📌Turn It Off - Disconnect from digital devices Give your work brain a rest.

📌Trim, Trim, Trim Saying “no” is an important step to creating balance in your life. 

📌Pay Attention to Your Health -Higher productivity and happiness lives in the balance of enough sleep, healthy eating and physical activity.

📌Minimize Toxins - Avoid toxic people (too negative and always complaining). If you can’t completely avoid them, at least minimize contact and tune them out as much as you can. Best to surround yourself with positive, supportive, can-do people whenever possible.

📌Explore the World - Get outside for a walk and really take in your surroundings. Try out a new route to work, visit a new place or play tourist in your hometown. 

📌Relationships Do Matter - Set aside quality time for your family and friends. This is very important as I get older. I carve out time to spend quality time with people I care about. 

#balance #lifewellbalanced

🌴 If you’re looking for scenic beaches in San Diego to enjoy your walks, here are some of my favorites: 🏖️

1. Pacific Beach: Known for its lively atmosphere, Pacific Beach offers a long stretch of sandy beach ideal for walking. You can enjoy beautiful ocean views while strolling along the boardwalk, which is lined with shops, restaurants, and cafes.

3. Sunset Cliffs: As the name suggests, Sunset Cliffs offers breathtaking views of the Pacific Ocean during sunset. This coastal area features rugged cliffs, hidden coves, and tide pools. Take a leisurely walk along the cliffside paths while taking in the natural beauty and catching glimpses of surfers and seabirds.

4. La Jolla: La Jolla is famous for its crystal-clear waters, sea caves, and vibrant marine life. It also offers a beautiful coastal walk. Stroll along the shoreline, admire the rugged cliffs, and keep an eye out for seals and sea lions.

These scenic beaches in San Diego provide different experiences, so you have plenty of options. Enjoy your walks and soak in the coastal beauty! 🌊

💦 Refreshing, hydrating, and bursting with flavor – this is the ultimate thirst-quencher to beat the heat! ☀️🔥 Get ready to fall in love with the taste of summer! 

here’s a simple recipe:

Ingredients:
- 4 cups of watermelon chunks (seedless)
- Juice of 1 lemon
- 1 cup sparkling water
- 1-2 tablespoons of honey (adjust to taste)
- Ice cubes
Optional - chamoy rim & tajin

Instructions:
1. Start by blending the watermelon chunks in a blender until smooth.
2. Strain the watermelon puree through a fine-mesh sieve or cheesecloth to remove any pulp or seeds.
3. In a pitcher, combine the strained watermelon juice, lemon juice, sparkling water, and honey. Stir well to mix all the ingredients together.
4. Taste the mixture and adjust the sweetness by adding more honey if desired.
5. Fill glasses with ice cubes and pour the watermelon refresher over the ice.
6. Garnish with a small watermelon wedge or a slice of lemon if desired. Or add chamoy rim with tajin.
7. Serve immediately and enjoy!

Feel free to adjust the ingredients according to your taste preferences. You can also add mint leaves or basil leaves for added freshness. Cheers

Filipino Arroz a La Cubana Recipe is inspired by Spanish ground beef dish. Filipinos added more sides with fried bananas, rice and over easy eggs. Adding sweet and savory flavors. It’s definitely a comfort food of mine.

- 1 lb Ground beef 
- 2 tbsp olive oil
- 1/4 onion, peeled and minced
- 2 cloves garlic, peeled and minced
- 1 cup tomato sauce
- 1/2 cup soy sauce
- 1/4 cup sugar
- 1/2 cup frozen sweet peas, thawed
- Salt and pepper to taste

**For the Sides:**

- Ripe but firm saba bananas
- Eggs
- Steamed white rice

**Instructions:**

1. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
2. Add minced onion and garlic, sautéing until they become fragrant and translucent.
3. Incorporate the ground beef into the skillet, breaking it apart with a spoon as it browns.
4. Once the beef is fully cooked, stir in tomato sauce, soy sauce, and sugar. Let the mixture simmer for a few minutes to meld the flavors.
5. Add the thawed sweet peas to the skillet, stirring to combine.
6. Season the mixture with salt and pepper according to your taste preferences.
7. In a separate pan, fry the saba bananas until they're golden and slightly caramelized. Set aside.
8. Using the same pan, fry the eggs to your desired level of doneness.
9. Serve the Arroz Cubano by placing a generous portion of steamed white rice on a plate. Top it with the savory ground beef mixture, a fried egg, and a side of fried saba bananas.

#filipinodish #recipe

For the dough:
-1 cup of gluten free flour
-1 tsp of xanthan gum
-1 tsp of baking powder
-1 pasteurized egg
-1 cup of almond milk
-1/2 cup of dairy free butter
 
For the toppings:
-1 cup of baking sweetener or 1/2 cup sugar

-In a baking mixer bowl - add flour, xanthan gum, baking powder, egg, almond milk, dairy free butter. Mix altogether until you get a dough consistency. Let it sit for 15 minutes. Then start rolling into a small ball.
 
-Set air fryer at 320 degrees, add donut holes, and cook for 20-25 minutes.
 
-Toppings - in a large bowl add baking sweetener & cinnamon, mix it together. Then add donut holes.
 
-Optional to dip donut holes into a melted chocolate

Get ready for a flavor explosion with these scrumptious Baked Beef Flautas! 🥩🔥 Perfectly seasoned Laura’s Lean Ground Beef, wrapped in warm tortillas, and baked to golden perfection. Top it off with creamy Avocado Cream, fresh tomatoes, onions, and cilantro for the ultimate fiesta in your mouth! 🥑🍅🌿

Ingredients:
- 1 lb Laura’s Lean Ground Beef
- 1/2 tsp cumin
- 1/2 tsp oregano
- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1 tbsp avocado oil cooking spray
- 2 tbsp fresh lime juice
- 1 avocado
- Pinch of salt (to taste)
- 1/2 cup sour cream (or non-dairy sour cream)
- 12 6-inch corn or flour tortillas (use corn tortillas for a gluten-free option)
- For Toppings:
 - Avocado Cream
 - 1/2 diced fresh tomato
 - 1/4 fresh diced onion
 - 1/2 cup cilantro

Directions:
1️⃣ Preheat your oven to 425 degrees.

2️⃣ In a sizzling pan, spray high-heat avocado oil and cook Laura’s Lean Ground Beef until it’s irresistibly brown. Sprinkle in cumin, oregano, and garlic powder for that flavor-packed punch!

3️⃣ Assemble the Flautas: Spoon about 2 tbsp of the beef mixture onto each tortilla, roll them up tightly, and place seam-side down on a baking pan or sheet.

4️⃣ Line up all your little flavor bundles, and give them a fantastic spray of avocado oil on top.

5️⃣ Bake your creations in the oven for 20 minutes or until they reach a glorious golden brown perfection.

6️⃣ While they’re baking, whip up the Avocado Cream: Blend fresh lime juice, avocado, salt, and sour cream until it’s a creamy dream.

7️⃣ Once your Flautas are out of the oven, top them with Avocado Cream, diced tomatoes, onions, and a sprinkle of cilantro.

Indulge in the ultimate no-bake treat: Oreo Peppermint Truffles! 😍🍫✨ These decadent delights require just a handful of ingredients:

- 39 regular Oreo cookies (441g)
- 8 oz cream cheese (227g), room temp
- 3/4 tsp peppermint extract
- 16 oz semisweet chocolate (454g), finely chopped
- 1 tbsp coconut oil or vegetable oil
- 2 candy canes, finely crushed

Here’s how to whip them up:
1️Blend Oreos in a food processor. Add cream cheese & peppermint; blend until smooth.
2️Scoop mixture into balls on a lined baking sheet or roll by hand.
3️ Freeze balls for at least 1 hour.
4️Melt chocolate & oil in bursts, stirring until smooth.
5️Coat chilled balls in chocolate, sprinkle crushed candy canes, and chill.
6️Voila! Enjoy these irresistible truffles chilled for up to 15 days. 😋👌
